  "texts": [
    "the response itself as a risk factor 38.",
    "This can lead to a highly nontrivial decision-making feedback loop.",
    "In other words, based on the decisions that are taken upon a warning, vulnerabilities and impacts may change, which therefore would change the warning.",
    "For example, an air pollution health impact forecast would be most useful if it considered not only the number of affected people if no action were taken, but also the same number under an evacuation plan in place.",
    "This requires the modeling of sociology and psychology, which, especially in combination with physical modeling, is challenging."
  ]
}